  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Multisectoral Support and COVID-19 Risk Mitigation for Displaced Populations in Saden and Qoloji IDPs Sites in Ethiopia</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The project aims to contribute to a well-coordinated, informed, and timely response to COVID-19 in Gambella and Tigray Regional States. For this, IOM is enhancing the capacity of Humera and Pagak points of entry in the areas of surveillance, infection prevention and control and risk communication.  IOM will also be empowering individuals and communities to adopt preventative and health seeking behaviours necessary for reducing the spread of the coronavirus and improving access to non-food items and essential health and protection services for targeted returnees, refugees, and asylum seekers.</narrative>
  </description>
